13⁷ Me, too, you have possessed among your many loves—but me with no reproach. Regret it not— twice you have fought for the sake of me. In tears Achelous gathered up his horns on the wet banks of his stream, and bathed in its clayey tide his mutilated brow; the half-man Nessus sank down in lotus- bearing Euenus, tingeing its waters with his equine blood.a But why am Ι reciting things like these? Even as I write comes rumour to me saying my lord is dying of the poison from my cloak. Alas me! what have I done? Whither has madness driven me in my love? O wicked Deianira, why hesitate to die?
